# üïµÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è Python Man-in-the-Middle (MITM) Tool

A lightweight Python script designed to perform ARP poisoning-based Man-in-the-Middle (MITM) attacks on local networks. This tool enables interception and analysis of network traffic between a target device and the gateway.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Features

- **ARP Poisoning**: Redirects traffic between a specified target and gateway.
- **MAC Address Resolution**: Utilizes the `manuf` library to identify device manufacturers.
- **Command-Line Interface**: Offers flexible options for specifying targets and gateways.

---

